:"Turku ja Pori, Finland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Svärd","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Henri, Jean-Claude, Remy.","French and Swiss French: shortened form of   Evrard  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Evrard","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alain, Emile, Herard, Jean Claude, Jean-Marc, Jeanmarie, Marcel.","French and Walloon: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Eberhard</i> (see   Eberhardt  ).","English: variant of   Everett  ."]}]},{"name":"Herman","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of  <b>Hermann</b>  , from a Germanic personal name derived from <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’. The name was in use among the Normans and was borne by many immigrants from the Low Countries in the 15th century. Perhaps because of that it continued in occasional use well into the 1700s. It was revived more generally in Britain in the 19th century, when it also became common in America, most probably as a result of the influence of German immigrants."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Herman Svärd was born in 1330, in Germany as the son of Herr Schwert. He married Birgitta Jacobsdotter Kurki in 1368, in Uusimaa, Finland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. He died in 1383, in Finland, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1330–1383":"1330–1383","1340–1370":"1340–1370","1360–1400":"1360–1400","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","1371–1428":"1371–1428","–Female":"Surnud","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1383":"1383","1371":"1371","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1305":"1305","Abt 1360":"umbes 1360","Abt 1371":"umbes 1371","1368":"1368","1400":"1400","1365":"1365","about 1365":"umbes 1365","1428":"1428","Suomi":"Soome","Uusimaa, Suomi":"Uusimaa, Soome","Lauko, Bjärnå, Turku Pori, Finland":"Perniö, Turku ja Pori, Soome","Finland